<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Rounding_to_integer">Roundi=
ng to integer</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DRounding&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Round=
ing to integer"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>]</span></span></div>
<p>The most basic form of rounding is to replace an arbitrary number by an =
integer. All the following rounding modes are concrete implementations of a=
n abstract single-argument "round()" procedure. These are true functions (w=
ith the exception of those that use randomness).
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Directed_rounding_to_an_int=
eger">Directed rounding to an integer</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/w/index.php?title=3DRounding&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=
=3D"Edit section: Directed rounding to an integer"><span>edit</span></a><sp=
an class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>These four methods are called <b>directed rounding to an integer</b>, as=
 the displacements from the original number <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" st=
yle=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> to the rounded value <span class=3D"tex=
html mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> are all directed toward or=
 away from the same limiting value (0, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Extended_real_number_line" title=3D"Extended real number line">+=E2=88=
=9E</a>, or =E2=88=92=E2=88=9E). Directed rounding is used in <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interval_arithmetic" title=3D"Interval arithmet=
ic">interval arithmetic</a> and is often required in financial calculations=
.
</p><p>If <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span=
> is positive, round-down is the same as round-toward-zero, and round-up is=
 the same as round-away-from-zero. If <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D=
"font-style:italic;">x</span> is negative, round-down is the same as round-=
away-from-zero, and round-up is the same as round-toward-zero. In any case,=
 if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> is a=
n integer, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</spa=
n> is just <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</spa=
n>.
</p><p>Where many calculations are done in sequence, the choice of rounding=
 method can have a very significant effect on the result. A famous instance=
 involved a new <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stock_index" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Stock index">index</a> set up by the <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vancouver_Stock_Exchange" title=3D"Vancouver S=
tock Exchange">Vancouver Stock Exchange</a> in 1982. It was initially set a=
t 1000.000 (three decimal places of accuracy), and after 22 months had fall=
en to about 520, although the market appeared to be rising. The problem was=
 caused by the index being recalculated thousands of times daily, and alway=
s being truncated (rounded down) to 3 decimal places, in such a way that th=
e rounding errors accumulated. Recalculating the index for the same period =
using rounding to the nearest thousandth rather than truncation corrected t=
he index value from 524.811 up to 1098.892.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rounding#cite_note-4"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
</p><p>For the examples below, <span class=3D"texhtml">sgn(<i>x</i>)</span>=
 refers to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sign_function" titl=
e=3D"Sign function">sign function</a> applied to the original number, <span=
 class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Rounding_down">Rounding dow=
n</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DRounding&a=
mp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Rounding down"><sp=
an>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></d=
iv>
<p>One may <b>round down</b> (or take the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Floor_and_ceiling_functions" title=3D"Floor and ceiling function=
s">floor</a></b>, or <b>round toward negative infinity</b>): <span class=3D=
"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> is the largest integer=
 that does not exceed <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">x</span>.
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e y=3D\mathrm {floor} (x)=3D\left\lfloor x\right\rfloor =3D-\left\lceil -x\=
right\rceil }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">f</mi>
          <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">l</mi>
          <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">o</mi>
          <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">o</mi>
          <mi mathvariant=3D"normal">r</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8B</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=88</mo>
          <mrow>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=89</mo>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle y=3D\mathrm {=
floor} (x)=3D\left\lfloor x\right\rfloor =3D-\left\lceil -x\right\rceil }</=
annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/fb15e838ef21768bbe169e93a80635276c941d79" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:29.131ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle y=
=3D\mathrm {floor} (x)=3D\left\lfloor x\right\rfloor =3D-\left\lceil -x\rig=
ht\rceil }"></span></dd></dl>
<p>For example, 23.7 gets rounded to 23, and =E2=88=9223.2 gets rounded to =
=E2=88=9224.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Rounding_up">Rounding up</h=
4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DRounding&amp;a=
ction=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Rounding up"><span>edi=
t</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>One may also <b>round up</b> (or take the <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Floor_and_ceiling_functions" title=3D"Floor and ceiling funct=
ions">ceiling</a></b>, or <b>round toward positive infinity</b>): <span cla=
ss=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> is the smallest i=
nteger that is not less than <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-sty=
le:italic;">x</span>.
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e y=3D\operatorname {ceil} (x)=3D\left\lceil x\right\rceil =3D-\left\lfloor=
 -x\right\rfloor }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>ceil</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=88</mo>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mo>=E2=8C=89</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
          <mrow>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8B</mo>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle y=3D\operator=
name {ceil} (x)=3D\left\lceil x\right\rceil =3D-\left\lfloor -x\right\rfloo=
r }</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/5d41b4578efb5b8fc96e0b07e21b6af68a7cb7ca" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:27.741ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle y=
=3D\operatorname {ceil} (x)=3D\left\lceil x\right\rceil =3D-\left\lfloor -x=
\right\rfloor }"></span></dd></dl>
<p>For example, 23.2 gets rounded to 24, and =E2=88=9223.7 gets rounded to =
=E2=88=9223.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Rounding_toward_zero">Round=
ing toward zero</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DRounding&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Roun=
ding toward zero"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">]</span></span></div>
<p>One may also <b>round toward zero</b> (or <b><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Truncation" title=3D"Truncation">truncate</a></b>, or <b>roun=
d away from infinity</b>): <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style=
:italic;">y</span> is the integer that is closest to <span class=3D"texhtml=
 mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> such that it is between 0 and =
<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> (include=
d); i.e. <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span>=
 is the integer part of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:it=
alic;">x</span>, without its fraction digits.
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e y=3D\operatorname {truncate} (x)=3D\operatorname {sgn}(x)\left\lfloor \le=
ft|x\right|\right\rfloor =3D-\operatorname {sgn}(x)\left\lceil -\left|x\rig=
ht|\right\rceil =3D{\begin{cases}\left\lfloor x\right\rfloor &amp;x\geq 0\\=
[5mu]\left\lceil x\right\rceil &amp;x&lt;0\end{cases}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>truncate</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>sgn</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
        <mrow>
          <mo>=E2=8C=8A</mo>
          <mrow>
            <mo>|</mo>
