<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" titl=
e=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"This is surprising. A confus=
ion with ''round half away from zero''? (June 2017)">citation needed</span>=
</a></i>]</sup> That is, half-way values of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" st=
yle=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> are always rounded up. If the fractiona=
l part of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span=
